        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 9 at 7:57PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 757 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Palisade, or 7 miles south of Hayes Center, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayes Center, Quick, Bluegill Haven Campground, Willow View
Campground, and Red Willow Reservoir State Recreation Area.

This includes Highway 83 between mile markers 27 and 43.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
southwestern Nebraska.</instruction>
